Parable of the Blind. L. Lebeer, Het Hooi en de hooiwagen in de beeldende kunsten, Gentsche Bijdragen V, 1938. The etching 1559 by Frans Hogenberg, published probably by B. de Mompere, repr. p. 151. Here in bottom at right corner, NÂ° 29, 2 slim elongated men falling from a little bridge into a brook quite different from Bruegel but to be mentioned; p. 154. A greatly altered copy of this etching engraved in 1608 by Gent artist Jacques Horenbault, 'Jacques Horenbault fecit et excud.1608' [...] Important inscription for each reprinted and discussed by J. column4: <content>Parable of the Blind. L. Lebeer, Het Hooi en de hooiwagen in de beeldende kunsten, Gentsche Bijdragen V, 1938. Here in bottom at right corner, N° 29, 2 slim elongated men falling from a little bridge into a brook quite different from Bruegel but to be mentioned; p. 154. A greatly altered copy of this etching engraved in 1608 by Gent artist Jacques Horenbault, 'Jacques Horenbault fecit et excud.1608' [...] Important inscription for each reprinted and discussed by J. Grauls, p. 156-174.</content>
